+- One intermediate Step-5 repair note still lists
+  `Lambda_cross = 1/12`.
+  I do **not** use that draft value.
+  The controlling Step-5 final result and the Step-5 shortlist memo both
+  freeze the repaired leakage vector at
+  `(1/4, 1/12, 1/12, 1/16, 1/24)`.
+
+## Findings
+
+### Shared Frozen Ledger Inherited Into Step 6
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Packet semantics remain the canonical one-bridge role-labeled
+  helical packet family
+  `P_n = (A_n, B_n, C_n, D_n, E_n)`
+  with mandatory conjugate completion.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The shared desired-channel core remains
+  `A -> B`,
+  `A -> C`,
+  `B,C -> C`,
+  `C,A <-> D`,
+  `D,D -> E`,
+  and the frozen spectator classes remain
+  `mirror`,
+  `companion`,
+  `feedback`,
+  `cross`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The canonicalization policy remains:
+  one conjugate-representative convention,
+  one helical basis convention,
+  one role-label ordering,
+  one amplitude normalization anchor with `|A_n(0)| = 1`,
+  one phase anchor with `arg A_n(0) = 0`,
+  and one family-declared helical sign sheet.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The fixed window remains the normalized activation window
+  `I = [0, 1]`,
+  with active families transported to
+  `int_I D_on(t) dt = 1`.
+
+### Survivor 1 - Repaired `Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Exact criterion:
+
+  ```text
+  Fix the role hierarchy
+  (h_seed, h_clk, h_amp, h_rot, h_next) = (1/16, 1/4, 1, 2, 2)
+  and eps_ref = 1/64.
+
+  Let F_h(A,B,C,D,E)
+    := (
+         -h_rot C D - h_clk A B - h_seed A C,
+          h_clk A^2 - h_amp C^2,
+          h_seed A^2 + h_amp B C,
+          h_rot C A - h_next D E,
+          h_next D^2
+       ).
+
+  Let
+  ||X||_role
+    := max(
+         |X_A|,
+         h_clk^(-1) |X_B|,
+         h_seed^(-1) |X_C|,
+         h_rot^(-1) |X_D|,
+         h_next^(-1) |X_E|
+       ).
+
+  Define
+  Delta_tmpl(P_n; I)
+    := sup_{t in I}
+       || Pi_{P_n} N(u,u)(t) - F_h(U_{P_n}(t)) ||_role
+       /
+       ( || F_h(U_{P_n}(t)) ||_role + eps_ref ),
+
+  Delta_spec(P_n; I)
+    := sup_{t in I}
+       || Pi_{S_n} N(u,u)(t) ||_role
+       /
+       ( || F_h(U_{P_n}(t)) ||_role + eps_ref ).
+  ```
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Repaired thresholds:
+
+  ```text
+  Delta_tmpl <= lambda_tmpl = 1/4
+  Delta_spec <= lambda_spec = 49/256.
+  ```
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Packet semantics:
+  same shared frozen ledger above; no change to packet class, channel list,
+  spectator partition, sign sheet, or window.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Carried-friendly witness:
+  `F_SL(1/16)`,
+  because it is the worst recorded friendly packet on both repaired defect
+  coordinates.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Hostile comparator:
+  `F_DT(delta, eta)`,
+  which remains a hostile failure on this gate by late rotor / next-shell
+  collapse on the same frozen ledger.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Invariant downstream gate:
+
+  ```text
+  G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec).
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Step-6 status:
+  promote unchanged.
+
+### Survivor 2 - Repaired `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Exact criterion:
+
+  ```text
+  Let
+  D_on(t)
+    := |Q_clk(t)| + |Q_seed(t)| + |Q_amp(t)|
+       + |Q_rot^A(t)| + |Q_rot^D(t)| + |Q_next(t)|.
+
+  Partition forced off-template channels into
+  S_mirror, S_companion, S_feedback, S_cross.
+
+  Set
+  D_off^class(t) := sum_{r in S_class} |Q_r(t)|,
+  D_off(t)       := D_off^mirror + D_off^companion
+                    + D_off^feedback + D_off^cross.
+
+  Then
+  L_class(P_n; I)
+    := int_I D_off^class(t) dt / int_I D_on(t) dt,
+  L_tot(P_n; I)
+    := int_I D_off(t) dt / int_I D_on(t) dt.
+  ```
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Repaired thresholds:
+
+  ```text
+  L_tot       <= 1/4
+  L_mirror    <= 1/12
+  L_companion <= 1/12
+  L_feedback  <= 1/16
+  L_cross     <= 1/24.
+  ```
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Packet semantics:
+  same shared frozen ledger above, with the same fixed spectator partition and
+  same `D_on` / `D_off` interaction currency.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Carried-friendly stress set:
+  `F_SS(1/12)` together with `F_SL(1/16)`,
+  because the repaired classwise budgets are saturated sharply only by the pair
+  rather than by a single recorded friendly family.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Hostile comparator:
+  `F_DT(delta, eta)`,
+  which remains a hostile failure on this gate by classwise leakage overload
+  on the same frozen ledger.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Invariant downstream gate:
+
+  ```text
+  G_leak(P_n; I)
+    = (L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross).
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Step-6 status:
+  promote unchanged.
+
+### Distinctness Decision
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The local record supports
+  **two distinct promoted downstream objects**,
+  not one narrowed object and not a bounded negative memo.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The Step-6 chain instructions explicitly say not to force a
+  single global notion unless the evidence really supports it.
+  No such dominance relation is landed locally.
+- `[INFERRED]` These survivors are not duplicate packaging on the frozen
+  ledger for four exact reasons:
+  1. `G_tmpl` and `G_leak` are different invariant gates on the same packet:
+     one compares the packet to a fixed Tao-like five-channel template through
+     the defect pair `(Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)`,
+     while the other compares off-template mass to desired-channel mass through
+     the classwise leakage sheet
+     `(L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)`.
+  2. `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` does **not** control
+     `Delta_tmpl`.
+     A packet can keep low spectator ratios yet still miss the desired-channel
+     template hierarchy or channel balance.
+     The local record contains no transfer lemma from classwise leakage pass to
+     template-defect pass.
+  3. `Template-Defect Near-Closure` does **not** control the repaired leakage
+     vector.
+     Its second coordinate `Delta_spec` is one aggregate off-template defect in
+     role norm, not the four-class integrated budget sheet.
+     The local record contains no transfer lemma from that aggregate defect to
+     the classwise leakage ratios.
+  4. The carried-friendly and hostile records stay different:
+     template defect sharpens against one worst friendly witness
+     `F_SL(1/16)` and one hostile late-rotor / next-shell collapse,
+     while leakage sharpens against a two-family friendly stress set and one
+     hostile classwise overload sheet.
+- `[INFERRED]` A forced one-object collapse would therefore violate the local
+  meta rule to collapse labels only when one exact family or one exact burden
+  currency has already absorbed the others.
+  That absorption has not been proved here.
+
+### Inherited Background On The Discarded Itinerary Route
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` `pre-trigger delay filter` ->
+  `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` `next-stage transfer-start filter` ->
+  `not well-defined`.
+
+### No-Overclaim Guardrails
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Repaired `Template-Defect Near-Closure` currently permits:
+  freezing one repaired defect-admissibility object on the audited packet
+  class, with witness `F_SL(1/16)`, hostile comparator `F_DT(delta, eta)`, and
+  downstream gate `G_tmpl(P_n; I)`.
+  It does **not** yet justify any claim that defect-pass automatically yields
+  the repaired classwise leakage sheet, a theorem, or a global exact Tao
+  circuit beyond the audited packet class and witnesses.
+- `[INFERRED]` Repaired `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` currently permits:
+  freezing one repaired classwise admissibility object on the same audited
+  packet class, with stress set `F_SS(1/12)` and `F_SL(1/16)`, hostile
+  comparator `F_DT(delta, eta)`, and downstream gate `G_leak(P_n; I)`.
+  It does **not** yet justify any claim that leakage-pass forces
+  template-defect pass, rotor / next-stage success, or a theorem without an
+  additional transfer lemma or next-stage exact test on the same ledger.
+
+## Failed Attempts and Dead Ends
+
+- Treating the intermediate Step-5 repair note as controlling is a dead end.
+  It would carry forward the older `Lambda_cross = 1/12` draft and thereby
+  reopen the repair pass against the explicit Step-5 final result.
+- Collapsing the two survivors into one downstream object is a dead end on the
+  current record.
+  The local dossier never proves that one repaired gate dominates the other in
+  the same burden currency.
+
+## Provisional Decision
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Final decision:
+  promote
+  repaired `Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+  and repaired `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
+  as two distinct downstream objects on the repaired Step-5 ledger.
+- `[INFERRED]` No narrowing or rejection is earned.
+  If one were to force a single promoted object, the only plausible bucket
+  would be a `usefulness` attack on the template-defect object because the
+  leakage screen is the clearest obstruction-facing gate.
+  The local record does **not** earn that attack, since
+  `Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+  still keeps its own exact invariant observable, repaired thresholds, hostile
+  failure mode, and carried-friendly witness.
+
+## Required Background Status
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Discarded itinerary route inherited into Step 6:
+  `pre-trigger delay filter` ->
+  `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`,
+  `next-stage transfer-start filter` ->
+  `not well-defined`.
+
+## No-Overclaim Guardrails
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Each promoted object remains confined to:
+  the canonical one-bridge role-labeled helical packet family with mandatory
+  conjugate completion,
+  the frozen spectator partition,
+  the frozen sign / phase / normalization sheet,
+  the fixed window `I = [0, 1]`,
+  the carried-friendly witnesses already on record,
+  and one invariant downstream gate on that same audited ledger.

