+### Distinctness Decision
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The local record supports
+  **two distinct promoted downstream objects**,
+  not one narrowed object and not a bounded negative memo.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The Step-6 chain instructions explicitly say not to force a
+  single global notion unless the evidence really supports it.
+  No such dominance relation is landed locally.
+- `[INFERRED]` These survivors are not duplicate packaging on the frozen
+  ledger for four exact reasons:
+  1. `G_tmpl` and `G_leak` are different invariant gates on the same packet:
+     one compares the packet to a fixed Tao-like five-channel template through
+     the defect pair `(Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)`,
+     while the other compares off-template mass to desired-channel mass through
+     the classwise leakage sheet
+     `(L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)`.
+  2. `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` does **not** control
+     `Delta_tmpl`.
+     A packet can keep low spectator ratios yet still miss the desired-channel
+     template hierarchy or channel balance.
+     The local record contains no transfer lemma from classwise leakage pass to
+     template-defect pass.
+  3. `Template-Defect Near-Closure` does **not** control the repaired leakage
+     vector.
+     Its second coordinate `Delta_spec` is one aggregate off-template defect in
+     role norm, not the four-class integrated budget sheet.
+     The local record contains no transfer lemma from that aggregate defect to
+     the classwise leakage ratios.
+  4. The carried-friendly and hostile records stay different:
+     template defect sharpens against one worst friendly witness
+     `F_SL(1/16)` and one hostile late-rotor / next-shell collapse,
+     while leakage sharpens against a two-family friendly stress set and one
+     hostile classwise overload sheet.
+- `[INFERRED]` A forced one-object collapse would therefore violate the local
+  meta rule to collapse labels only when one exact family or one exact burden
+  currency has already absorbed the others.
+  That absorption has not been proved here.
+
