+### No-Overclaim Guardrails
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Repaired `Template-Defect Near-Closure` currently permits:
+  freezing one repaired defect-admissibility object on the audited packet
+  class, with witness `F_SL(1/16)`, hostile comparator `F_DT(delta, eta)`, and
+  downstream gate `G_tmpl(P_n; I)`.
+  It does **not** yet justify any claim that defect-pass automatically yields
+  the repaired classwise leakage sheet, a theorem, or a global exact Tao
+  circuit beyond the audited packet class and witnesses.
+- `[INFERRED]` Repaired `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` currently permits:
+  freezing one repaired classwise admissibility object on the same audited
+  packet class, with stress set `F_SS(1/12)` and `F_SL(1/16)`, hostile
+  comparator `F_DT(delta, eta)`, and downstream gate `G_leak(P_n; I)`.
+  It does **not** yet justify any claim that leakage-pass forces
+  template-defect pass, rotor / next-stage success, or a theorem without an
+  additional transfer lemma or next-stage exact test on the same ledger.
+
